MonoBehaviour:
  m_ObjectHideFlags: 0
  m_CorrespondingSourceObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabInstance: {fileID: 0}
  m_PrefabAsset: {fileID: 0}
  m_GameObject: {fileID: 0}
  m_Enabled: 1
  m_EditorHideFlags: 0
  m_Script: {fileID: 11500000, guid: 70c970a7d9f7d414994564bd048e8a6d, type: 3}
  m_Name: UFO_Compelling_Military
  m_EditorClassIdentifier: KBTV.Runtime::KBTV.Dialogue.CallerDialogueTemplate
  Topic: {fileID: 0}
  Legitimacy: 3
  Priority: 2
  Length: 12
  IntroLines:
  - Text: Vern, I'm a retired Air Force pilot, and what I saw last week has kept
      me up every night since.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Twenty years flying fighters. I've seen everything that's supposed to be
      in our skies. This wasn't any of it.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I signed NDAs when I left the service. I'm breaking them tonight because
      people need to know.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  DetailLines:
  - Text: Radar contact at 40,000 feet, no transponder, performed maneuvers that
      would kill any human pilot. Command told us to forget it happened.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: We tracked it for eighteen minutes. It descended from 80,000 feet to sea
      level in under four seconds. Nothing we have can do that.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The craft was disc-shaped, metallic, approximately 40 feet in diameter.
      I was close enough to see the seams.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  DefenseLines:
  - Text: They can discredit me all they want. I have my flight logs, I have witnesses.
      This happened.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I've got nothing to gain from this and everything to lose. Why would I
      make it up?
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You think I want to be called crazy? I'm risking my pension for this.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  AcceptanceLines:
  - Text: That's exactly right. They don't want us talking about this.
    Tone: 7
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Finally, someone who understands what's at stake here.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: You're one of the few who gets it, Vern.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ExtraDetailLines:
  - Text: After we landed, men in suits were waiting on the tarmac. They took our
      recorders, our notes. Told us the mission never happened.
    Tone: 7
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I've talked to pilots from three other bases. Same story. Same craft. Same
      orders to stay quiet.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: The radar data was scrubbed within hours. But I kept a personal log. Old
      habit from my training days.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  ExtraDefenseLines:
  - Text: I've got copies of everything stored in three different locations. If something
      happens to me, it all goes public.
    Tone: 7
    Weight: 1
  - Text: My service record is spotless. Thirty years of distinguished service. I
      didn't throw that away to tell a story.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Two of my wingmen are prepared to corroborate. They're just waiting for
      the right moment.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  ConclusionLines:
  - Text: Keep doing what you're doing, Vern. The truth needs to get out.
    Tone: 9
    Weight: 1
  - Text: I've said my piece. Do with it what you will.
    Tone: 0
    Weight: 1
  - Text: Stay safe, Vern. They're listening.
    Tone: 7
    Weight: 1
